                               Introduction

   When I worked for Hokkaidou University (Faculty of Letters, 2010-2021), I 
guided many field excursions. This article is written based on my excursion 
notes. (by T. Nihei) #1
   In this article, place names are written as they are pronounced, for 
example, Hokkaido --> Hokkaidou. This is because Japanese place names are 
sometimes difficult to pronounce (Nihei lab 2024a).

   #1 As for field excursion, it is good for education. I still remember 
vividly teachers words I hear during field excursions 30 years ago. Words 
goes into the brain by the wind. Bus excursion is not always good because 
some students fall asleep.
 
